&lt;Enfield Corp Ltd> said it planned toissue 60 mln dlrs principal amount of notes and 1.6 mln class Epreferred shares at 25 dlrs a share.    The notes would bear 8 pct yearly interest, mature March31, 2002 and be convertible to common shares on either March31, 1997 or the business day before a fixed redemption date at13.50 dlrs a share, Enfield said.    It said each preferred share would be convertible to 1.85common shares on either March 31, 1997 or the business daybefore a fixed redemption date. Gordon Capital Corp andDominion Securities Inc agreed to acquire the issues, it said.    Enfield said it would use proceeds to retire short-termbank debt and boost its 22 pct stake in &lt;Consumers PackagingInc> and its interest in &lt;Federal Pioneer Ltd> through openmarket purchases. Reuter&#3;